venues.name: O2 Academy Bournemouth

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Call Box Office on 01202 399922 or email boxoffice@o2academybournemouth.co.uk
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: 12pm to 4pm, Monday to Friday by arrangement in advance, so please do get in touch with us, we're at your service. Opening times will be different on bank holidays, so do check.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Credit and Debit cards and cash.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets left for collection can be picked up on the door, on the day of the event, from when doors open. Please take the Ticketmaster reference number and the card used as payment with you.

venues.parkingDetail: Free on street parking can be found in the local area. Hawkwood Road main car park is long stay, use postcode BH5 1BY for sat nav. It has two disabled parking bays and is around 300 metres away. At weekends, the Sovereign Centre car park is just next door and is open until midnight on Friday and Saturday, charges apply.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: To book tickets for O2 Academy Bournemouth Please book your ticket through www.ticketweb.co.uk and then contact the venue on 01202 399922 or info@o2academybournemouth.co.uk to discuss arrangements and organise your companion ticket should one be required. After purchasing your ticker please contact the venue direct on 01202 399922 or email info@o2academybournemouth.co.uk with their booking number to discuss arrangements. You can also contact the box office through text relay by 18002 01202 399922 should this be required. Once you have been in contact with the venue you will be sent an email confirmation that should be printed off and brought with you when you attend the event. Spaces may be limited and will be sold on a first come first served basis.

generalInfo.generalRule: Non-professional camers are fine (no large lenses), no re-admission, no food and drink and no smoking.
generalInfo.childRule: Gigs: The minimum age is 8 unless with written permission from venue management. Under 14s must be accompanied by an adult. Under 18s events are 13 to 17yrs only Clubs: Strictly over 18s (Photographic ID will be required)

venues.name: Honda Center

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Box office phones are answered during regular box office hours. Please note, the box office does not sell tickets by phone. Call (714) 704-2500 for general information
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Monday through Friday 10am to 3pm. The box office will remain open through the beginning of weeknight events. On event Saturdays and event Sundays, the box office will open three (3) hours prior to the event and remain open through the beginning of the event. The box office is located on the east side of the building, near the East Entrance, facing the Santa Ana riverbed.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: American Express, Discover, MasterCard, and Visa are accepted. Honda Center is a cashless venue.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: A photo ID matching the name the tickets are placed under is required. VIP, Artist, Promoter, or other special will call requirements and locations are subject to change. Will call windows are located at the Box Office. Will call is generally available beginning 1-1/2 hours prior to the event, and closes after the start of the event (after the first intermission for Anaheim Ducks games). Late pick up will be available at the East Entrance after the box office closes.

venues.parkingDetail: We encourage guests to consider walking, biking, taking public transit, or carpooling to avoid traffic, save on gas and parking, and reduce your carbon footprint. General Parking: $25.00 Preferred Parking (if available): $35.00 Limo/RV/Bus Parking: $50.00. Additional information available at https://www.hondacenter.com/plan-your-visit/parking-directions/
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Wheelchair accessible seating is available in most areas of Honda Center including Plaza, Club, and Terrace levels. Availability of locations is dependent upon event seating configuration. For availability and exact locations based on a particular event, please toggle the Accessibility icon in the seat map filters on the Ticketmaster.com event page. The box office will have the same availability as Ticketmaster. Please note, semi-ambulatory or limited mobility seating is also available and requires the guest to navigate some steps. Wheelchair accessible seats have no steps. Hearing Impaired Guests: Assistive listening devices are available, with a picture ID as a deposit, at the Guest Services Desk located at Section 214. Requests for sign language interpreters must be received at least 14 business days prior to the event you are attending. To arrange for courtesy sign language interpreters, please either email accessibilityservices@hondacenter.com or call 714-704-2400. For a full list of ADA policies, please visit https://www.hondacenter.com/arena-info/ada-accessibility/

generalInfo.generalRule: Please visit https://www.hondacenter.com/arena-info/admission-requirements/ for current bag policy and admission requirements. You can also download the HONDA CENTER + DUCKS app to pre-purchase parking, order food & drinks for pickup directly from your seat, and manage tickets using your Ticketmaster.com account.Please visit https://www.hondacenter.com/arena-info/admission-requirements/ for current bag policy and admission requirements. You can also download the HONDA CENTER + DUCKS app to pre-purchase parking, order food & drinks for pickup directly from your seat, and manage tickets using your Ticketmaster.com account.
generalInfo.childRule: Children 23 months and under are free, if on parents lap. 2 years old and over must have a ticket. Child policy is subject to change on an event by event basis.
